feat(landing): procedural Web Audio score for the Stellar Genesis intro

Synthesizes the whole soundtrack with the Web Audio API (no sample files,
same all-procedural rule as the visuals): a deep space drone bed + star
shimmer, a tension riser and doppler whoosh for the meteor, a sub-bass
impact thump with a noise-burst explosion and reverb slam, a warm
major-chord pad swell for the genesis, and a resolving tail on handoff.
A convolution reverb is built from a decaying-noise impulse; a limiter
guards the master from the impact transient.

The engine is beat-driven off the timeline's onBeat callbacks, so it can
join the film mid-flight if sound is enabled late. Muted by default behind
a "Sound" toggle (browser autoplay needs a gesture); returning opt-in
listeners resume on first interaction. Suspends with the tab, disposes on
unmount.

Verified headlessly by tapping the AudioContext through an AnalyserNode:
context runs, no errors, and amplitude rises through omen, jumps on impact,
peaks on the genesis swell, then resolves.

